dismissalText.commentary: Usman Khawaja run out (BMAJ Mendis/†Chandimal) 3 (11b 0x4 0x6 18m) SR: 27.27

dismissalComment.html: Appeal fora run out and Khawaja is in trouble! And he's gone! Schoolboy error by Khawaja, credit to Jeevan Mendis for this one, Khawaja worked it towards short midwicket and set off, he turned back and had to dive at the crease, he made the mistake of not sliding with his bat face on the ground, Mendis swooped down and under-armed the throw to the keeper Chandimal, top stuff by Mendis

dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Chandimal c †Haddin b McKay 73 (95b 7x4 1x6 128m) SR: 76.84

dismissalComment.html: superb catch by Haddin! McKay pitched it up and bowled it wide of the off stump getting him to drive, thick outside edge and Haddin timed his dive to his right very well and plucked it one-handed. He nonchalantly tosses the ball away. Made it seem to easy, but it was one tough take!

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan run out (Khawaja) 51 (70b 4x4 0x6 104m) SR: 72.85

dismissalComment.html: Direct hit and Dilshan looks in trouble! Yes he is a mile out, it was a risky run, he pushed it towards mid-off and set off, Khawaja attacked the ball, picked up and hit the stumps direct at the bowler's end, the Australians all knew it

dismissalText.commentary: Lahiru Thirimanne run out (Maxwell/†Haddin) 0 (0b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Two run outs off successive  balls would you believe it! It's that man Maxwell again. Chandinal dropped it towards short cover and set off, hesitation in the running, Maxwell runs to his right, picks up and in one movement fires the ball to Haddin, Thirimanne is not in the frame

commentTextItems.html: it's all over, at the stroke of the 40th over! Catching practice for Haddin, Mendis gets a length ball which he presumably wants to dab to third man, only managed a thick edge, Haddin would have caught that with his eyes shut

commentPostTextItems.html: End of match: Comprehensive win for Australia. Outsmarted Sri Lanka in all departments, with a special mention for the fielding. Three run-outs, all specialist batsmen. Chandimal was the positive today for Sri Lanka, but had it not been for those run outs, this could have gotten closer. That's something SL need to address before their next match. Today was a communications disaster.
Richard : "Sorry. What was that about an Aussie B-side?"
It can't be too bad a team when you have the likes of Hughes, Khawaja and Finch in probably the form of his life. He didn't perform today but his time will come.
Phillip Hughes is the Man of the Match. We don't have coverage of the presentation.

Otherwise that's it from here. There's still the India-England ODI and the SA v NZ Test to keep you occupied. We're back for the second ODI at Adelaide in two days. Same time. Thanks for your company. Cheers!

pulls and it's in the air and he just clears midwicket

full outside off and he drives him down to cover

full on the off stump and he spoons it towards cover, had to scamper that single

headshotImage.longCaption: Usman Khawaja player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan run out (Khawaja) 51 (70b 4x4 0x6 104m) SR: 72.85

dismissalComment.html: Direct hit and Dilshan looks in trouble! Yes he is a mile out, it was a risky run, he pushed it towards mid-off and set off, Khawaja attacked the ball, picked up and hit the stumps direct at the bowler's end, the Australians all knew it

dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Chandimal c †Haddin b McKay 73 (95b 7x4 1x6 128m) SR: 76.84

dismissalComment.html: superb catch by Haddin! McKay pitched it up and bowled it wide of the off stump getting him to drive, thick outside edge and Haddin timed his dive to his right very well and plucked it one-handed. He nonchalantly tosses the ball away. Made it seem to easy, but it was one tough take!

dismissalText.commentary: Angelo Mathews run out (Maxwell) 12 (14b 0x4 0x6 17m) SR: 85.71

dismissalComment.html: Appeal for a run-out and Mathews is in trouble and the direct hit sends him back! Tossed up and Chandimal drops it to the off side, the striker tells Mathews to stay back, Mathews was already a few yards in front and had to turn back and Maxwell hits the stumps at the bowler's end

dismissalText.commentary: Lahiru Thirimanne run out (Maxwell/†Haddin) 0 (0b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Two run outs off successive  balls would you believe it! It's that man Maxwell again. Chandinal dropped it towards short cover and set off, hesitation in the running, Maxwell runs to his right, picks up and in one movement fires the ball to Haddin, Thirimanne is not in the frame

dismissalText.commentary: Jeevan Mendis c Bailey b Johnson 20 (18b 1x4 1x6 23m) SR: 111.11

dismissalComment.html: soft dismissal! Length ball skids through and Mendis tries to launch it over the bowler's head, not in control and he miscues it to mid-off, easy catch to Bailey

dismissalText.commentary: Thisara Perera c Bailey b Johnson 4 (8b 0x4 0x6 24m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: straight to mid-off! It was the off cutter from Johnson, he makes room and spoons it flat and fast to Bailey who takes a low catch
